org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.graph

Interface IGraph<V,E extends IGraphEdge<V>>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - Type of vertices in the graph.
    E - Type of edges in the graph
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Graph, SynchronizedGraph

    public interface IGraph<V,E extends IGraphEdge<V>>
    Interface to a generic graph. Vertices can be any old type of object. Edge's must implement IGraphEdge. There may only be a single directional edge from any vertex to any other vertex. For example, there can be an edge from A to B and another edge from B to A. However it is impossible to store a second edge from A to B.
